objects.Disp_Title: 13. Kelmscott Manor: Bed Morris Was Born In
objects.Info_Page_Comm: Kelmscott Manor is the 16th - 17th century Oxfordshire country home of William Morris (1834-1896), the British artist most often associated with the English Arts and Crafts movement. William Morris Gallery caption: "Jane Morris' bedroom (belonging to the wife of William Morris) is directly above the Green Room.  The early 19th century four-poster bed is the one in which William Morris was born, at Elm House, Walthamstow, on 24th March 1834.  Its hangings are in the "Small Stem" printed wool and cotton fabric, a pattern of the 1830s revived by Morris, Marshall, Faulkner & Company and produced from the late 1860s onwards."
objects.Dedication: Gift of Mary Peirce, Class of 1912
